Author: sandsandwich#3906
Content:
My calculations aren't making any sense for KMD. Anyone care to tell me where I am going wrong?

Using the standard equihash calculation gives me a way higher expected coins per day.
I assume the komodo stake is messing me up

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: `the standard equihash calculation` assumes you have a possible 1440 blocks per day to get, but you only have 25-30% of that

Author: sandsandwich#3906
Content: Due to the notary nodes correct?

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: yes

Author: sandsandwich#3906
Content: if that's the case, then is there any accurate way to adjust my calculations? Do the normal equihash calculation then times it by 0.25/0.3 for my coins per day?

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: if you have small amount of hash, lean more towards calc * 0.2 if you have large lean more towards 0.25 or 0.28

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: on average the blocks come out to be about 25% for miners, but with reward blocks, we tend to get another 3-10% over a year

Author: sandsandwich#3906
Content: Is the block reward consistently 3 for miners?

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content:
3+ tx fees
+ any unclaimed rewards in a tx

Author: sandsandwich#3906
Content:
Ah ok I see.
Im looking  to short term mine KMD but the profitability doesnt seem to be beneficial for me

Author: sandsandwich#3906
Content: Feel I must be overlooking something

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: short-term mining KMD will likely never be profitable in a bear market

Author: sandsandwich#3906
Content: Thanks for your time, you were super helpful
